<br>
I know what you mean about having to force money on some clerics though. The /s works if you are in a group with them. If not, then you have to be more creative. I have found that most clerics who refuse money won't turn down peridots. <br>
<br>
That reminds me...everybody go buy a stack of peridots. If you are in a group with a cleric and want Temp/Aego/Virtue, hand them a peridot. One dungeon crawl should not cost a cleric 50-100p and win or lose, they will remember a group fondly if they aren't eating the cost of buffing everyone. I have had some groups take the cost of gems off the top at the end, but many people seem to ignore the cost. That may have something to do with the expense of a rez these days.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kimberlyfv>Kimberly FV</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.pages.at/iceman/Anime/anime66.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Erudite Debutante</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/24/03 8:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4088.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.pages.at/iceman/Anime/anime66.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: odd</span><hr size=1> Roose said <br>
&quot;am i the only one that has to FORCE money on my clerics? (always has to load with pp and then do a /split to pay em)&quot;<br>
<br>
I had a bad pull in Dreadlands the other day and I was so upset with myself, I hate dying in an outdoor zone its so foolish. But a root stopped me in my tracks and I had no pet up!<br>
<br>
Anyway, it was early in the morning and no cleric in zone so I did the dreaded /join market and said I would donate for a rez in the Dreadlands, not expecting any response.<br>
<br>
Soon an extremely nice man sent me a tell, ran all the way from the FV book to the hidden valley, and used his AA 100% rez on me, buffed me with Virtue, and REFUSED to take any payment or even a peridot.<br>
<br>
Whoever that guy's RL girlfriend is, she's the luckiest gal alive!<br>
What a sweetheart!<br>
<br>
Clerics are the best, most giving people ever!<br>
<br>
