<br>
There is no unstated price, but you're right, it is kind to pay well if you are bringing someone away from a group, over a long distance, or into danger.  <br>
<br>
If there is a corpse right by me (someone has dragged it, etc) and I'm not busy, I just rez it and decline payment.  (nice to donate or give a dot for buffs after though, if you are able).<br>
<br>
In other cases, I have now started more graciously accepting whatever plat the person feels is fair, since I'm saving for that darn 50k Hand of Virtue spell - lol.  If their 'donation' offer is over about 50pp, I am quite happy to throw in buffage on the house <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.chivalrousvalor.com/sigs/key.JPG" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
